Copy one restore point's closure from a backup into an empty destination root and commit it

Usage: sleet mirror restore [OPTIONS] <ROOT> <BACKUP> <DEST>

Arguments:
  <ROOT>
          Fleet root URL, e.g. s3://ops/sleet/

  <BACKUP>
          Backup root URL (a mirror destination)

  <DEST>
          Empty destination root URL

Options:
      --at <AT>
          The restore point: a manifest id or an RFC 3339 timestamp. Default: the backup's latest manifest

      --format <FORMAT>
          Output format

          Possible values:
          - text: Human-readable text
          - json: JSON matching the subcommand's response schema
          
          [default: text]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
